Greyhound Lines said, on its first dayunder new management, it slashed fares on 166 of its shorterroutes, many by 50 pct or more.    On Wednesday, Greyhound Corp &lt;G> completed the sale of itsGreyhound Lines subsidiary to GLI Holdings Inc for 350 mln dlrsin cash, securities, royalties and other considerations.    Most of the routes affected are 100 miles or less andconnect cities and towns throughout the country and includeroutes serving suburban terminals, colleges, military bases andresort locations. Reuter&#3;